# DOM Utilities - jQuery Replacement

Always use `dom` utility instead of jQuery:

## Element Selection
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.selector')
dom.find('.selector')

// Instead of: $('#id')  
dom.findOne('#id')

// Instead of: $('.selector').length > 0
dom.exists('.selector')
```

## Content Manipulation
```javascript
// Instead of: $('#id').text('content')
dom.text('#id', 'content')

// Instead of: $('#id').html('<span>content</span>')
dom.html('#id', '<span>content</span>')

// Instead of: $('#id').val('value')
dom.val('#id', 'value')
```

## Event Handling
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.btn').on('click', handler)
dom.on('.btn', 'click', handler)

// Event delegation:
dom.on('.container', 'click', handler, '.btn')
```

## CSS Classes
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.el').addClass('class')
dom.class('.el', 'class', 'add')

// Instead of: $('.el').removeClass('class')
dom.class('.el', 'class', 'remove')

// Instead of: $('.el').toggleClass('class')
dom.class('.el', 'class', 'toggle')
```

## Styles
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.el').css('color', 'red')
dom.css('.el', 'color', 'red')

// Multiple styles:
dom.css('.el', { color: 'red', fontSize: '16px' })
```